item.title: Tributes flow for Olympic hero
item.description: Tributes are flowing for Olympic hero Charles “Chilla” Porter who became a household name after his dramatic silver medal performance at the 1956 Melbourne Olympic Games.

item.title: Delivery driver carjacked at gunpoint
item.description: A delivery driver has been carjacked at gunpoint as he was making a drop off in Melbourne’s west.

item.title: Sex worker charged with hotel death
item.description: A Cairns woman will front court on Monday, charged with causing the death of a Brisbane businessman whose body was found in a north Queensland hotel.

item.title: Accused car thief ‘clocked at 220km/h’
item.description: A man is accused of reaching speeds of up to 220km/h during an alleged high speed police chase across Melbourne’s western suburbs before he arrested and hit with a coronavirus breach fine.

item.title: Heroic bystanders wrestle with armed robber
item.description: A heroic act from two bystanders was not enough to stop an armed robber from fleeing the scene of the alleged crime in Sydney’s southwest.

item.title: Three dead in Gold Coast crash
item.description: Three people have died and one is in a serious condition after a head-on collision at the Gold Coast on Sunday night.

item.title: Change to make it easier for tradies to work
item.description: Tradies will be able to go wherever the work is under red-tape-cutting reforms designed to make it easier to work interstate.

item.title: Trial HSC exams cancelled after virus case
item.description: A Sydney selective high school has been closed and had its trial HSC exams postponed after a student tested positive for COVID-19.

item.title: Brace for wet and wintry conditions
item.description: Wet weather is expected to hit Victoria and parts of southeastern Australia over the next week.
